{"title_page": "Ricco the Mean Machine", "text_new": "{{short description|1973 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ricco the Mean Machine\n| image          =   Ricco the Mean Machine.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| story       = \n| director       = [[Tulio Demicheli]]\n| producer      =   \n| writer  =  Mario Di Nardo <br /> Sebastiano Moncada <br /> Jos\u00e9 G. Maesso \n| starring       =  [[Christopher Mitchum]] <br /> [[Barbara Bouchet]]\n| music          =Nando De Luca\n| cinematography =  \tFrancisco Fraile\n| editing        = \n| distributor    =\n| released       = {{Film date|1973}} \n| runtime        =\n| country        =  \n| language       = Italian\n| budget         =\n}}\n\n'''''Ricco the Mean Machine''''' ({{lang-it|Un tipo con una faccia strana ti cerca per ucciderti}}, {{lang-es|Ajuste de cuentas}}, also known as '''''The Cauldron of Death''''' and '''''The Dirty Mob''''') is a 1973 Italian-Spanish [[crime film|crime-thriller film]] directed  by [[Tulio Demicheli]] and starring [[Christopher Mitchum]]  and  [[Barbara Bouchet]].<ref name=\"70-79 z\">{{cite book|author1=Roberto Chiti |author2=Roberto Poppi |author3=Enrico Lancia |title=Dizionario del cinema italiano: I film|publisher=Gremese, 1991|isbn=8876059695}}</ref>  It achieved some [[cult film|cult]] [[cult following|status]] because of its violent and gory scenes, including a graphic castration.<ref name=Curticrime>{{cite book|last1=Roberto Curti|title=Italian Crime Filmography, 1968-1980|publisher=McFarland, 2013|isbn=0786469765}}</ref> The US title was actually a misspelling of the main character's name Rico.<ref name=Curticrime>{{cite book|last1=Roberto Curti|title=Italian Crime Filmography, 1968-1980|publisher=McFarland, 2013|isbn=0786469765}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{expand section|date=August 2015}}\n\n==Cast==\n\n* [[Christopher Mitchum]] as Rico Aversi\n* [[Barbara Bouchet]] as Scilla Calogero\n* [[Malisa Longo]] as Rosa\n* [[Arthur Kennedy (actor)|Arthur Kennedy]] as Don Vito\n* [[Eduardo Fajardo]] as  Cirano\n* [[Paola Senatore]] as  Conchetta Aversi\n* [[Manolo Zarzo]] as Tony \n* [[Jos\u00e9 Mar\u00eda Caffarel]] as  The Marseillese\n* [[\u00c1ngel \u00c1lvarez]] as  Giuseppe Calogero\n* [[Luis Induni]] as  Gaspare Aversi\n* [[V\u00edctor Israel|Victor Israel]] as Checana\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|id=0068183}}\n\n[[Category:Italian crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Italian films]]\n[[Category:Spanish crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:1970s crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tulio Demicheli]]\n[[Category:Films set in Turin]]\n\n\n{{crime-thriller-film-stub}}\n{{1970s-Italy-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1973 film}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Ricco the Mean Machine\n| image          =   Ricco the Mean Machine.jpg\n| image_size     =\n| story       = \n| director       = [[Tulio Demicheli]]\n| producer      =   \n| writer  =  Mario Di Nardo <br /> Sebastiano Moncada <br /> Jos\u00e9 G. Maesso \n| starring       =  [[Christopher Mitchum]] <br /> [[Barbara Bouchet]]\n| music          =Nando De Luca\n| cinematography =  \tFrancisco Fraile\n| editing        = \n| distributor    =\n| released       = {{Film date|1973}} \n| runtime        =\n| country        =  \n| language       = Italian\n| budget         =\n}}\n\n'''''Ricco the Mean Machine''''' ({{lang-it|Un tipo con una faccia strana ti cerca per ucciderti}}, {{lang-es|Ajuste de cuentas}}, also known as '''''The Cauldron of Death''''' and '''''The Dirty Mob''''') is a 1973 Italian-Spanish [[crime film|crime-thriller film]] directed  by [[Tulio Demicheli]] and starring [[Christopher Mitchum]]  and  [[Barbara Bouchet]].<ref name=\"70-79 z\">{{cite book|author1=Roberto Chiti |author2=Roberto Poppi |author3=Enrico Lancia |title=Dizionario del cinema italiano: I film|publisher=Gremese, 1991|isbn=8876059695}}</ref>  It achieved some [[cult status]] because of its violent and gory scenes, 